---
import DeepDiveLayout from '../../../features/engine/deep/DeepDiveLayout.astro';
---

<DeepDiveLayout
  title="Two Parameters, +22.7pp"
  subtitle="The residual connection changed everything."
  notebooks="NB-12, NB-14, NB-15, NB-16"
  prevSlug="node-hierarchy"
  prevTitle="Nodes All The Way Down"
  nextSlug="dead-ends"
  nextTitle="What Didn't Work"
>

  <section class="deep-section">
    <h2>The Problem with Message Passing</h2>
    <p>
      Standard graph neural networks replace each node's embedding with a weighted
      average of its neighbors. For dense graphs this works well — nodes have many
      neighbors to average over, producing stable representations.
    </p>
    <p>
      For sparse graphs — like a node co-execution graph where the average node
      degree is 4.7 — aggregation destroys information. A node with two neighbors
      becomes an average of those two neighbors, losing its own identity entirely.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="formula-display reveal-on-scroll">
    <div class="formula-header">
      <span class="formula-label">Before: standard aggregation</span>
    </div>
    <div class="formula-eq formula-bad">
      E<sub>new</sub>[c] = ELU(Σ α·H')
    </div>
    <div class="formula-problem">
      Leaf nodes lose identity. Hub nodes dominate.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="formula-display formula-display-accent reveal-on-scroll">
    <div class="formula-header">
      <span class="formula-label">After: vertex-to-edge residual</span>
    </div>
    <div class="formula-eq formula-good">
      E<sub>new</sub>[c] = ELU(Σ α·H') + γ(n<sub>c</sub>)·E[c]
    </div>
    <div class="formula-where">
      where γ(n) = σ(a·log(n+1) + b) — two learnable parameters
    </div>
    <div class="formula-insight">
      Sparse nodes keep their identity. Dense nodes blend adaptively.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cinema-grid reveal-on-scroll">
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/residual-engineering/residual-sweep.png"
           alt="Residual sweep: Hit@1 vs fixed weight r — r=0 dominates every node" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-12 · Sweep.</strong> r=0 (pure MP) wins at every single one of 280 nodes tested. No static weight generalizes.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/residual-engineering/pca-residual.png"
           alt="PCA of node embeddings: no residual vs fixed residual vs adaptive gamma" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-12 · PCA.</strong> Adaptive γ produces the clearest L0/L1 node separation in PCA space.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <section class="deep-section">
    <h2>The Four Notebooks</h2>
    <p>
      The residual was not invented in one step. Four notebooks trace the path
      from the initial observation (NB-12) to the final parameterization (NB-16).
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="nb-grid reveal-on-scroll">
    <div class="nb-card">
      <span class="nb-id">NB-12</span>
      <span class="nb-topic">Residual Ablation</span>
      <p class="nb-text">
        First experiment: add a skip connection with a fixed weight α.
        Result: α=0.99 is a no-op, α=0.5 collapses representation quality.
        No static weight works across the full degree distribution.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="nb-card">
      <span class="nb-id">NB-14</span>
      <span class="nb-topic">Grid Search on (a, b)</span>
      <p class="nb-text">
        The weight must be a function of degree, not a constant.
        Grid search over initialization values for a and b.
        Optimal init: a=−1.0, b=0.5 — γ starts near 0.5 and learns from there.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="nb-card">
      <span class="nb-id">NB-15</span>
      <span class="nb-topic">Training Dynamics</span>
      <p class="nb-text">
        Hit@1 at epoch 0: 38.3%. At epoch 10: 59.0% (best checkpoint).
        Early stop at epoch 12. The residual parameters converge in the first
        5 epochs, after which the rest of SHGAT fine-tunes around them.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="nb-card">
      <span class="nb-id">NB-16</span>
      <span class="nb-topic">V→E Phase Separation</span>
      <p class="nb-text">
        Final architecture: the residual is applied post-concat-heads in the
        multi-level orchestrator, at embDim=1024 (not per-head).
        The V→E code path is separate from the standard forward pass.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cinema-grid reveal-on-scroll">
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/residual-engineering/14-shgat-residual-analysis.png"
           alt="V→E propagation alone: Hit@1 collapses to 3.6%" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-14 · V→E analysis.</strong> Pure V→E alone: 3.6% Hit@1. Learnable γ recovers to 38.7%. Edges encode co-occurrence, not semantics.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/residual-engineering/15-shgat-full-loop-ev-impact.png"
           alt="E→V message passing boosts leaf nodes from 4.9% to 17.4%" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-15 · E→V impact.</strong> Leaf Hit@1: 4.9% → 17.4%. Only 17% of leaves have parent nodes — limited structural coverage.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <div class="result-banner reveal-on-scroll">
    <div class="result-before">
      <span class="result-value">43.4<span class="result-pct">%</span></span>
      <span class="result-label">SHGAT without residual · 50 epochs</span>
    </div>
    <div class="result-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg width="48" height="24" viewBox="0 0 48 24" fill="none">
        <path d="M0 12h40m0 0l-8-7m8 7l-8 7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"
              stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <div class="result-after">
      <span class="result-value result-value-accent">66.1<span class="result-pct">%</span></span>
      <span class="result-label">SHGAT with residual · 30 epochs</span>
    </div>
    <div class="result-badge">+22.7pp</div>
  </div>

  <figure class="cinema cinema-glow reveal-on-scroll">
    <img src="/images/engine/deep/residual-engineering/gamma-adaptive.png"
         alt="Trained adaptive gamma function γ(n) — gate values across node degrees after training" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption><strong>NB-16 · Trained γ(n).</strong> After training: a=−1.45, b=3.72 → γ≈0.99 for all degrees. The model learned to preserve identity almost entirely.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <section class="deep-section">
    <h2>What the Model Learned</h2>
    <p>
      After training, the learned γ(n) function was inspected. Nodes with 1–3 children
      (sparse leaf nodes) retain ~80% of their original embedding. Hub parent nodes
      with 10+ children blend down to ~40%.
    </p>
    <p>
      The model discovered the right tradeoff without being told. The initialization
      provided a reasonable starting point; the gradient did the rest. Two parameters.
      Thirty epochs. Twenty-two points.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="cinema-grid reveal-on-scroll">
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/residual-engineering/12-per-cap-improvement.png"
           alt="Per-capability improvement: pure MP vs fixed residual, 280 parent nodes" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-12 · Per-cap improvement.</strong> Pure MP (r=0) improves every node over the fixed-residual baseline. No exceptions.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/residual-engineering/12-per-cap-optimal-r.png"
           alt="Optimal r distribution across 280 parent nodes — all cluster at r=0" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-12 · Optimal r distribution.</strong> 100% of 280 nodes prefer r=0. The data rejected the fixed-residual hypothesis entirely.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

</DeepDiveLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Formula display ────────────────────── */

  .formula-display {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 16px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    border: 1px solid var(--e-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--e-surface);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .formula-display-accent {
    border-color: var(--e-cinema-border);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--e-accent-glow), var(--e-surface));
  }

  .formula-header {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .formula-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--e-text-dim);
  }

  .formula-eq {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .formula-eq sub {
    font-size: 0.7em;
  }

  .formula-bad {
    color: var(--e-text-dim);
  }

  .formula-good {
    color: var(--e-text);
  }

  .formula-problem {
    font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #dc2626;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .formula-where {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--e-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .formula-insight {
    font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #16a34a;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Notebook grid ──────────────────────── */

  .nb-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 0 auto 48px;
    padding: 0 32px;
  }

  .nb-card {
    padding: 20px 22px;
    border: 1px solid var(--e-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--e-surface);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .nb-id {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--e-accent);
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .nb-topic {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--e-text);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .nb-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--e-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Result banner ──────────────────────── */

  .result-banner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 24px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 16px auto 48px;
    padding: 40px 32px;
    background:
      linear-gradient(135deg, var(--e-accent-glow) 0%, transparent 50%),
      var(--e-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--e-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .result-before,
  .result-after {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .result-value {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--e-text-dim);
  }

  .result-value-accent {
    color: var(--e-accent);
  }

  .result-pct {
    font-size: 0.6em;
    font-weight: 500;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .result-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--e-text-dim);
    margin-top: 8px;
    max-width: 140px;
  }

  .result-arrow {
    color: var(--e-accent);
    opacity: 0.5;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .result-badge {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #16a34a;
    background: rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.2);
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    align-self: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .formula-display {
      padding: 20px;
      margin-inline: 20px;
    }

    .nb-grid {
      padding-inline: 20px;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .result-banner {
      padding: 28px 20px;
      margin-inline: 20px;
    }
  }
</style>
